latestIgtvVideos.title: @childmindinstitute #gettingbettertogether
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Thankfully through social media, we can learn about new resources. Ones like the @childmindinstitute who do amazing and inspiring work in raising awareness in the Mental Health field. May, being #mentalhealthawareness month, felt like a good opportunity to share my tiniest tid bit of my own experience dealing with anxiety. Let’s encourage children and adolescents to take advantage of resources like childmind.org. Now more than ever in pandemic, social media, modern day crazy times, reaching out for help and guidance is the very best thing you can do to keep you and your brain healthy 🧠 ✌🏻

Even though we premiered at TIFF, there’s something uniquely special about sharing a film at home—in your own city, surrounded by friends and family. It just hits different.
Last night was emotional and a true full-circle moment seeing my family in the audience. 
Thank you to everyone who came out to support.
Gonzo Girl will be out in the world very, very soon.

latestPosts.caption:
@camilamorrone is Alley, an aspiring writer and Walker Reade’s determined assistant.

#GonzoGirlFilm #Tribeca2025

SOMETHING VERY *GOOD* JUST HAPPENED. 
We wrapped SOMETHING VERY BAD!!!! I’ve basically been sleeping since then, so please excuse me taking a second to gather my thoughts — and my emotions.
73 day shoot. 
Canadian winter. *if you know, you know* Blood — plenty of it. Not a lot of sweat.  Snow. More blood. Nights that bled into mornings. Then more nights.  Then more snow. And in the middle of it all, tears. Blend of joy and delirium and exhaustion.
We gave it everything. 
I don’t know exactly what’s on the table — but I know I’m DAMN proud of it. And even more proud of the people it took to make it real.
To the cast, the crew- THANK YOU. You carried this thing through fire and snow. 
Friends for life. 
We did it. 
Coming to @netflix in 2026❤️🩸
